<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-03T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-03T04:00:00-05:00" n="640" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d640">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 862.6131/14</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WHR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-03T10:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 3, 1918, 10 a.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received March 4, 9.12
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2765. French military attaché informs me that under <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_HK1">Helfferich</persName>’s
                                leadership Germans have founded a provisioning bureau in
                                Constantinople which is organizing purchase of wheat and other grain
                                in Ukraine which is routed to Odessa and Crimean ports. All barges
                                obtainable, even in Holland, have been bought to carry grain up the
                                Danube.</p>
                            <pb facs="0770" n="1604" xml:id="pg_1604"/>
                            <p>Bureau has representative in Berne and has offered grain to
                                Switzerland in return for her economic independence. Meeting of
                                Federal Council held last night to consider sending Swiss
                                representative to Ukraine. Decision not known.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WHR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>